<item>
            <title>[HBASE-426] hbase can&apos;t find remote filesystem</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-426</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If filesystem is remote, e.g. its an Hadoop DFS running &quot;over there&quot;, there is no means of pointing hbase at it currently (unless you count copying hadoop-site.xml into hbase/conf).  Should be possible to just set a fully qualified hbase.rootdir and that should be sufficient for hbase figuring the fs (needs to be backported to 0.1 too).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12388144">HBASE-426</key>
